commit.message:
Makefile.in (C_AND_C_OBJS): Add ggc-callbacks.o.

	* Makefile.in (C_AND_C_OBJS): Add ggc-callbacks.o.
	(OBJS): Add $(GGC).
	(ggc-callbacks.o): New target.
	* ggc-callbacks.c: New file.

From-SVN: r29113

files.patch:

+#include "config.h"
+#include "system.h"
+#include "rtl.h"
+#include "tree.h"
+#include "ggc.h"
+
+void 
+lang_mark_tree (t)
+     union tree_node *t ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED;
+{
+  /* If this function is called, we are doing GC.  But, this file is
+     only included in compilers for languages that don't support GC.  */
+  abort ();
+}
+
+void
+lang_cleanup_tree (t)
+     union tree_node *t ATTRIBUTE_UNUSED;
+{
+  /* If this function is called, we are doing GC.  But, this file is
+     only included in compilers for languages that don't support GC.  */
+  abort ();
+}
